 <tr style="mso-yfti-irow:6;mso-yfti-lastrow:yes;height:31.0pt">
  <td width="749" valign="top" style="width: 513pt; border-right-width: 1pt; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-right-color: black; border-bottom-color: black; border-image: initial; border-top: none; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 31pt;">
  <p class="HPBullet10pt"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:
  Symbol;color:#262626;mso-font-kerning:10.0pt">·<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;color:#262626">This configuration
  variable decide whether to preserve the values of monitored objects and
  session variables for opcmona. If it preserve the values, opcmona can get
  these values even after it restarts.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:
  Symbol;color:#262626;mso-font-kerning:10.0pt">·<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;color:#262626">For example, let’s
  assume there is a Monitoring threshold policy with threshold 10.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:2.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
  2.0pt;margin-left:0in;text-autospace:none;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:
