  <td width="749" valign="top" style="width: 513pt; border-right-width: 1pt; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-right-color: black; border-bottom-color: black; border-image: initial; border-top: none; background: rgb(242, 242, 242); padding: 0in 5.4pt;">
  <p class="Label"><span style="font-size:12.0pt">Short description</span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;
  mso-bidi-font-family:Arial"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr style="mso-yfti-irow:4;height:40.9pt">
  <td width="749" valign="top" style="width: 513pt; border-right-width: 1pt; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-right-color: black; border-bottom-color: black; border-image: initial; border-top: none; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 40.9pt;">
  <p class="HPBullet10pt"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:
  Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:#2E74B5;mso-themecolor:accent1;
  mso-themeshade:191;mso-font-kerning:10.0pt">·<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;color:#262626">This variable decides
  if perl interpreter needs to be retained persistently in memory or should be loaded
  and unloaded for each instance of execution of embedded perl script in
  policies</span><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Calibri Light&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(46, 116, 181); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"> <o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr>
  <td width="749" valign="top" style="width: 513pt; border-right-width: 1pt; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-right-color: black; border-bottom-color: black; border-image: initial; border-top: none; background: rgb(242, 242, 242); padding: 0in 5.4pt;">
  <p class="Details"><b>Long description</b><span class="DetailsChar"><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:
  major-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:major-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial"><o:p></o:p></span></b></span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr style="mso-yfti-irow:6;mso-yfti-lastrow:yes;height:31.0pt">
  <td width="749" valign="top" style="width: 513pt; border-right-width: 1pt; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-right-color: black; border-bottom-color: black; border-image: initial; border-top: none; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 31pt;">
  <p class="HPBullet10pt"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:
  Symbol;color:#262626;mso-font-kerning:10.0pt">·<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;color:#262626">Default value in
  windows is “FALSE” and default value for unix is “TRUE”<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:
  Symbol;color:#262626;mso-font-kerning:10.0pt">·<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;color:#262626">OPC_MON_KEEP_PERSISTENT_PERL_ENGINE
  value decides if perl script embedded within policy is executed with eval_pv
  perl api.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:
  Symbol;color:#262626;mso-font-kerning:10.0pt">·<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;color:#262626">Details of the above
  api found in the below link<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;tab-stops:9.35pt;
  mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:around;
  mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;mso-element-left:9.0pt;mso-element-top:
  -38.25pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span class="MsoHyperlink"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif"><a href="http://perldoc.perl.org/perlembed.html">http://perldoc.perl.org/perlembed.html</a></span></span><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;color:#262626"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:
  normal;mso-outline-level:2;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;
  mso-element-wrap:around;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;mso-element-left:
  9.0pt;mso-element-top:-38.25pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><a name="_Toc491176800"></a><a name="_Toc478414207"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;
  mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri;
  mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#262626">Snapshot from above
  link</span></a><span style="font-size:10.0pt;mso-ascii-font-family:
  Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri;
  mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#262626"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:
  Symbol;color:#262626;mso-font-kerning:10.0pt">·<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;color:#262626">Perl provides two API
  functions to evaluate pieces of Perl code. These are eval_sv in perlapi and
  eval_pv in perlapi.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:
  Symbol;color:#262626;mso-font-kerning:10.0pt">·<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;color:#262626">Arguably, these are
  the only routines you'll ever need to execute snippets of Perl code from
  within your C program. Your code can be as long as you wish; it can contain
  multiple statements; it can employ use, require, and do to include external
  Perl files.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;tab-stops:9.35pt;
  mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:around;
  mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;mso-element-left:9.0pt;mso-element-top:
  -38.25pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;
  color:#262626">eval_pv lets us evaluate individual Perl strings, and then
  extract variables for coercion into C types<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;tab-stops:9.35pt;
  mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:around;
  mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;mso-element-left:9.0pt;mso-element-top:
  -38.25pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;
  color:#262626">&nbsp;</span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;tab-stops:9.35pt;
  mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:around;
  mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;mso-element-left:9.0pt;mso-element-top:
  -38.25pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;
  color:#262626">The use of the config variable is to decide if perl
  interpreter needs to be maintained persistently or loaded for each execution
  of the embedded perl script<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;tab-stops:9.35pt;
  mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:around;
  mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;mso-element-left:9.0pt;mso-element-top:
  -38.25pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;
  color:#262626">More details on the persistent interpreter can be found in the
  below link<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;tab-stops:9.35pt;
  mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:around;
  mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;mso-element-left:9.0pt;mso-element-top:
  -38.25pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span class="MsoHyperlink"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif"><a href="http://perldoc.perl.org/perlembed.html#Maintaining-a-persistent-interpreter">http://perldoc.perl.org/perlembed.html#Maintaining-a-persistent-interpreter</a></span></span><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;color:#262626"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;tab-stops:9.35pt;
  mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:around;
  mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;mso-element-left:9.0pt;mso-element-top:
  -38.25pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;
  color:#262626">Snapshot from the above link<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;tab-stops:9.35pt;
  mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:around;
  mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;mso-element-left:9.0pt;mso-element-top:
  -38.25pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;
  color:#262626">&nbsp;</span></p>
  <p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:
  9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:around;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;
  mso-element-left:9.0pt;mso-element-top:-38.25pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size:9.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:#515151">When
  developing interactive and/or potentially long-running applications, it's a
  good idea to maintain a persistent interpreter rather than allocating and
  constructing a new interpreter multiple times. The major reason is speed:
  since Perl will only be loaded into memory once.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:
  9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:around;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;
  mso-element-left:9.0pt;mso-element-top:-38.25pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size:9.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:#515151">If
  perl interpreter persistent option is not set to true eval api is executed
  each time the embedded perl script is executed.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:
  9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:around;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;
  mso-element-left:9.0pt;mso-element-top:-38.25pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size:9.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:#515151"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;tab-stops:9.35pt;
  mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:around;
  mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;mso-element-left:9.0pt;mso-element-top:
  -38.25pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;
  color:#262626">&nbsp;</span></p>
  <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:2.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
  2.0pt;margin-left:0in;text-autospace:none;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:
  9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:around;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;
  mso-element-left:9.0pt;mso-element-top:-38.25pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span class="DetailsChar"><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: &quot;Calibri Light&quot;, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></span></p><table class="MsoNormalTable" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="left" width="0" style="border-left: none; margin-left: 0.1in; margin-right: 0.1in;">
 <tbody><tr>
  <td width="749" valign="top" style="width: 513pt; border-top: none; border-right: none; border-left: none; border-image: initial; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-bottom-color: black; padding: 0in 5.4pt;">
  <p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
  </td>
