 <tr>
  <td width="749" valign="top" style="width: 513pt; border-right-width: 1pt; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-right-color: black; border-bottom-color: black; border-image: initial; border-top: none; background: rgb(242, 242, 242); padding: 0in 5.4pt;">
  <p class="Label"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial">Short Description<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr style="mso-yfti-irow:3;height:40.9pt">
  <td width="749" valign="top" style="width: 513pt; border-right-width: 1pt; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-right-color: black; border-bottom-color: black; border-image: initial; border-top: none; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 40.9pt;">
  <p class="HPBullet10pt"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: windowtext; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">OPC_OPCMON_NETSNMP_SESSION_TIMEOUT config variable is used to set
  maximum time opcmona process can wait to get SNMP MIB data.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr>
  <td width="749" valign="top" style="width: 513pt; border-right-width: 1pt; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-right-color: black; border-bottom-color: black; border-image: initial; border-top: none; background: rgb(242, 242, 242); padding: 0in 5.4pt;">
  <p class="Details"><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:
  &quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:major-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:
  major-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;color:windowtext">Long Description</span></b><span class="DetailsChar"><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial"><o:p></o:p></span></b></span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr style="mso-yfti-irow:5;mso-yfti-lastrow:yes;height:31.0pt">
  <td width="749" valign="top" style="width: 513pt; border-right-width: 1pt; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-right-color: black; border-bottom-color: black; border-image: initial; border-top: none; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 31pt;">
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="margin-left:0in;text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;
  tab-stops:9.35pt;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:
  around;mso-element-anchor-vertical:page;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;
  mso-element-left:9.0pt;mso-element-top:.05pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span class="DetailsChar"><span style="font-size: 11pt; color: black; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">When opcmona process
  monitors SNMP MIB Measurement threshold policy, It try to fetch the MIB data
  every interval and check for the threshold and perform necessary action.<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="margin-left:0in;text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;
  tab-stops:9.35pt;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:
  around;mso-element-anchor-vertical:page;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;
  mso-element-left:9.0pt;mso-element-top:.05pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span class="DetailsChar"><span style="font-size: 11pt; color: black; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Opcmona process fetch the
  MIB data by opening snmp session and request snmp Query and get the data and
  close the snmp session.<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="margin-left:0in;text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;
  tab-stops:9.35pt;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:
  around;mso-element-anchor-vertical:page;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;
  mso-element-left:9.0pt;mso-element-top:.05pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span class="DetailsChar"><span style="font-size: 11pt; color: black; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">By Default opcmona wait
  for 2 second to get the MIB data and close the session.<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="margin-left:0in;text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;
  tab-stops:9.35pt;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:
  around;mso-element-anchor-vertical:page;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;
  mso-element-left:9.0pt;mso-element-top:.05pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span class="DetailsChar"><span style="font-size: 11pt; color: black; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="margin-left:0in;text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;
  tab-stops:9.35pt;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:
  around;mso-element-anchor-vertical:page;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;
  mso-element-left:9.0pt;mso-element-top:.05pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span class="DetailsChar"><u><span style="font-size: 11pt; color: black; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Possible
  Scenarios where&nbsp;
  OPC_OPCMON_NETSNMP_SESSION_TIMEOUT&nbsp;
  variable could be used</span></u></span><span class="DetailsChar"><span style="font-size: 11pt; color: black; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"> :<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="margin-left:0in;text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;
  tab-stops:9.35pt;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:
  around;mso-element-anchor-vertical:page;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;
  mso-element-left:9.0pt;mso-element-top:.05pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span class="DetailsChar"><span style="font-size: 11pt; color: black; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Sometime opcmona need to
  get the MIB data from Remote node as well. During this scenario there is
  possibility of delay in receiving the MIB data from the remote node and
  opcmona policy fails with the below error in System.txt.<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="margin-left:0in;text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;
  tab-stops:9.35pt;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:
  around;mso-element-anchor-vertical:page;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;
  mso-element-left:9.0pt;mso-element-top:.05pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span class="DetailsChar"><span style="font-size: 11pt; color: black; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="margin-left:0in;text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;
  tab-stops:9.35pt;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:
  around;mso-element-anchor-vertical:page;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;
  mso-element-left:9.0pt;mso-element-top:.05pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span class="DetailsChar"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <i>Initialization
  of MIB source SNMPsource failed. (OpC30-726)<o:p></o:p></i></span></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;tab-stops:9.35pt;
  mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:around;
  mso-element-anchor-vertical:page;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;
  mso-element-left:9.0pt;mso-element-top:.05pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span class="DetailsChar"><i><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">&nbsp;
  Collect data from SNMP source SNMPsource failed. (OpC30-719)<o:p></o:p></span></i></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="margin-left:0in;text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;
  tab-stops:9.35pt;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:
  around;mso-element-anchor-vertical:page;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;
  mso-element-left:9.0pt;mso-element-top:.05pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span class="DetailsChar"><i><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Can't issue an SNMP GET request for monitor.<o:p></o:p></span></i></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="margin-left:0in;text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;
  tab-stops:9.35pt;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:
  around;mso-element-anchor-vertical:page;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;
  mso-element-left:9.0pt;mso-element-top:.05pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span class="DetailsChar"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="margin-left:0in;text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;
  tab-stops:9.35pt;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:
  around;mso-element-anchor-vertical:page;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;
  mso-element-left:9.0pt;mso-element-top:.05pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span class="DetailsChar"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">To Overcome this situation
  we can use OPC_OPCMON_NETSNMP_SESSION_TIMEOUT config variable to increase the
  number of second the snmp session can be opened to get the MIB data from the
  remote node.<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
</tbody></table>
  <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:2.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
