 <tr>
  <td width="749" valign="top" style="width: 513pt; border-right-width: 1pt; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-right-color: black; border-bottom-color: black; border-image: initial; border-top: none; background: rgb(242, 242, 242); padding: 0in 5.4pt;">
  <p class="Label"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial">Short Description<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr style="mso-yfti-irow:3;height:40.9pt">
  <td width="749" valign="top" style="width: 513pt; border-right-width: 1pt; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-right-color: black; border-bottom-color: black; border-image: initial; border-top: none; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 40.9pt;">
  <p class="HPBullet10pt"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: windowtext; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">OPC_THREAD_STACK_SIZE config
  variable is used to set stack size of opcmona threads. Default value is for
  this config variable is </span><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:
  &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: windowtext; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Linux ( 524288),AIX( 262144),SOLARIS
  and HPUX( 5242880)<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr>
  <td width="749" valign="top" style="width: 513pt; border-right-width: 1pt; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-right-color: black; border-bottom-color: black; border-image: initial; border-top: none; background: rgb(242, 242, 242); padding: 0in 5.4pt;">
  <p class="Details"><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif;
  mso-ascii-theme-font:major-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:major-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:
  Arial;color:windowtext">Long Description</span></b><span class="DetailsChar"><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:
  Arial"><o:p></o:p></span></b></span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr style="mso-yfti-irow:5;mso-yfti-lastrow:yes;height:31.0pt">
  <td width="749" valign="top" style="width: 513pt; border-right-width: 1pt; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-right-color: black; border-bottom-color: black; border-image: initial; border-top: none; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 31pt;">
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="margin-left:0in;text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;
  tab-stops:9.35pt;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:
  around;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;mso-element-left:9.0pt;
  mso-element-top:-38.25pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span class="DetailsChar"><span style="font-size: 11pt; color: black; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Opcmona
  process creates each thread per opcmona policy deployed in the node.<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="margin-left:0in;text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;
  tab-stops:9.35pt;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:
  around;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;mso-element-left:9.0pt;
  mso-element-top:-38.25pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span class="DetailsChar"><span style="font-size: 11pt; color: black; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">When new
  thread is getting created, thread allocate memory space to hold the
  information of the program variables in the memory space called “Stack Memory
  Region”.<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="margin-left:0in;text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;
  tab-stops:9.35pt;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:
  around;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;mso-element-left:9.0pt;
  mso-element-top:-38.25pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span class="DetailsChar"><span style="font-size: 11pt; color: black; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">This stack
  memory gets freed once the thread is stopped.<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="margin-left:0in;text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;
  tab-stops:9.35pt;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:
  around;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;mso-element-left:9.0pt;
  mso-element-top:-38.25pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span class="DetailsChar"><span style="font-size: 11pt; color: black; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></span></p>
  <p class="Default"><u><span style="font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-theme-font:
  minor-bidi;color:windowtext">Possible Scenarios where&nbsp; OPC_THREAD_STACK_SIZE variable could be
  used :<o:p></o:p></span></u></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="margin-left:0in;text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;
  tab-stops:9.35pt;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:
  around;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;mso-element-left:9.0pt;
  mso-element-top:-38.25pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span class="DetailsChar"><span style="font-size: 11pt; color: black; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">There can be a
  situation that when opmona policy is needed more memory to store the program
  variable but stack memory allocated to the thread is less. Opcmona process
  abort with the “Stack Overflow” error. <o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="margin-left:0in;text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;
  tab-stops:9.35pt;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:
  around;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;mso-element-left:9.0pt;
  mso-element-top:-38.25pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span class="DetailsChar"><span style="font-size: 11pt; color: black; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">To avoid the
  opcmona abort we can use the config variable to increase the thread stack
  size.<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
  <p class="HPBullet10pt" style="margin-left:0in;text-indent:0in;mso-list:none;
  tab-stops:9.35pt;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:
  around;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;mso-element-left:9.0pt;
  mso-element-top:-38.25pt;mso-height-rule:exactly"><span class="DetailsChar"><span style="font-size: 11pt; color: black; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Maximum value
  that can be set to the OPC_THREAD_STACK_SIZE is 10 MB.</span></span><span class="DetailsChar"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: windowtext; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
</tbody></table>
  </td>
